"title": "5377: law, Ten Commandments",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5377: law, ten commandments",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The basic laws given to Israel through Moses following the exodus from Egypt (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:1-Exod20:17\">Ex 20:1–17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6-Deut5:21\">Dt 5:6–21</a>). The first four commandments safeguard Israel's special relation to God; the remaining six protect individuals within the community and promote their well-being.</p>\n<h2>The Ten Commandments are to govern the life of Israel as the people of God</h2>\n<h3>Israel should obey God alone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:2-Exod20:3\">EXO 20:2–20:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6-Deut5:7\">DEU 5:6–5:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13-Deut6:15\">DEU 6:13–6:15</a></p>\n<h3>Idolatry forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:4-Exod20:6\">EXO 20:4–20:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:8-Deut5:10\">DEU 5:8–5:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:1-Exod32:8\">EXO 32:1–32:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:4\">LEV 19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:7\">1CO 10:7</a></p>\n<h3>God's name should not be misused</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:7\">EXO 20:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:11\">DEU 5:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:21\">MAT 7:21</a></p>\n<h3>A day of rest is commanded</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:11\">EXO 20:8–20:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12-Deut5:15\">DEU 5:12–5:15</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:23\">EXO 16:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:3\">LEV 19:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:2\">ISA 56:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:21-Jer17:22\">JER 17:21–17:22</a></p>\n<h3>Parents are to be honoured</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16\">DEU 5:16</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:4\">MAT 15:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1-Eph6:3\">EPH 6:1–6:3</a></p>\n<h3>Murder is forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:13\">EXO 20:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:17\">DEU 5:17</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:8-Gen4:16\">GEN 4:8–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:21\">MAT 5:21</a></p>\n<h3>Adultery is forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:14\">EXO 20:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:18\">DEU 5:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:20\">LEV 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:5\">2SA 11:2–11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:27\">MAT 5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:4\">HEB 13:4</a></p>\n<h3>Stealing is forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:15\">EXO 20:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:19\">DEU 5:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:11\">LEV 19:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:13\">LEV 19:13</a></p>\n<h3>False witness is forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:16\">EXO 20:16</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:20\">DEU 5:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:11\">LEV 19:11</a></p>\n<h3>Coveting is forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:17\">EXO 20:17</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:21\">DEU 5:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:17-Lev19:18\">LEV 19:17–19:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:9-Job31:12\">JOB 31:9–31:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:7\">ROM 7:7</a></p>\n<h2>The circumstances surrounding the giving of the Ten Commandments</h2>\n<h3>The Ten Commandments written on stone tablets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:12\">EXO 24:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:13\">DEU 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:9-Deut9:10\">DEU 9:9–9:10</a></p>\n<h3>The stone tablets broken</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19\">EXO 32:19</a></strong> <em>Moses broke the stone tablets when he saw that the Israelites had sinned by making the golden calf.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:16-Deut9:17\">DEU 9:16–9:17</a></p>\n<h3>A second set of stone tablets made</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1\">EXO 34:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:28\">EXO 34:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:1-Deut10:2\">DEU 10:1–10:2</a></p>\n<h3>The second set of stone tablets put in the ark of the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:20\">EXO 40:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:1-Deut10:2\">DEU 10:1–10:2</a></p>",
